Hi Rennie,

Yes, both clutch cables had a short piece of plastic on them with what I
believe to be  a part number on them. Oddly the new cable had a piece that
said 431 380 17 10, the one I replaced had a piece that said 431 380 0105.
The new one fit, and seems to be working fine. 
As far as the piece of plastic tube I was asking about- this was different.
It was about as long as the bowden tube, and came out of the bowden tube
when I pulled the clutch cable out of the bowden tube. This was the 2nd time
I have pulled the cable out of the tube in the past few weeks. Last time
this piece of plastic was not present. I was thinking that maybe this is was
a sleeve that goes inside the bowden tube to allow the cable to slide, but
it had broken/split due to insufficient lubrication on the cable.
I guess at the end of the day, I'm wondering if I should be replacing my
bowden tube too?
I should have cleaned out the tube like you suggest, I never thought of
that-thanks for the tip. I also reused the clevis pin, lot of lube on it.
I'll revisit this when I go to replace the bushings and seals on the shift
rod linkages...
What rubber booty are you talking about?

Thanks for the tips...

