Clutch cables used to come with a short piece of plastic tube on them. They
had an identifier on them. Might have been used to segregate during
production. 

Always check the 'hook' at the front. The hole could be worn, which changes
the adjustment drastically. Always replace the clevis pin with each cable. 

When I replace the cable, I always use the old cable to clean out the tube.
With a drill, you can clean the tube of all the crap that has accumulated
from the road. Replacing the rubber booty helps a lot too. 

Rennie
